    "In most bins we observe modest biases: amplitudes are typically ᾱ ≲ 0.2, and vary smoothly over the plane of resolution and S/N.",
    "However, in low S/N cases the A170, page 30 of 54 Wright, A. H., et al.",
    ": A&A, 686, A170 (2024) Notes.",
    "Superscript indices specify whether a number refers to sources that are removed from the sample ('r') or kept in the sample ('k').",
    "N r s is the total number of sources (from the full MASK ≤ 1 sample) that are flagged for removal by the selection s. f r tot is N r s expressed as a fraction of the full MASK ≤ 1 sample (N k MASK)."
